  "type": "Manifest",
  "label": {
    "none": [
      "Florida area cumulus experiment of 1978 : environmental impact statement."
    ]
  },
  "summary": {
    "none": [
      "The Florida Area Cumulus Experiment (FACE) of 1978 aimed to increase rainfall in South Florida using cloud seeding. This research, led by NOAA, sought to confirm earlier findings that dynamic seeding could enhance convective rainfall. The experiment was extended for two more years, with the goal of achieving up to 60 experimental days. While the project had minimal environmental impact, concerns were raised about potential effects on local agriculture, particularly tomatoes, and the broader ecosystem if applied long-term. The experiment was closely coordinated with local agricultural interests to mitigate any adverse effects."
    ]
  },
