      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Historical Context"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The Florida Area Cumulus Experiment (FACE) was proposed to explore the potential of cloud seeding to increase rainfall in South Florida, an area often affected by drought. While the project aimed to enhance rainfall for agricultural benefits, there were concerns from the public and local farmers about the possible long-term impacts on crops and the environment. Ultimately, the experiment was conducted with careful coordination with agricultural stakeholders to address these concerns, and it was deemed to have minimal environmental impact."
        ]
      }
    },
